Package org.eng.aisp.feature

Defines a framework for features and the operations on them including extractiong and processing.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDoubleFeature Deprecated
    in favor of IFeature
    IFeature<FDATA>
    A marker interface that is really just an ISuperDataWindow.
    IFeatureGram<FDATA>
    Contains an array of features, generally computed from subwindows of a single IDataWindow.
    IFeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>  
    ILabeledFeatureGram<FDATA>
    Contains an array of features, generally computed from subwindows of a single IDataWindow, together with the labels from the source IDataWindow.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DoubleFeature
    An implementation of IDoubleFeature.
    FeatureGram<FDATA>
    Contains an array of features, generally computed from subwindows of a single IDataWindow.
    FeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Implements the full feature extraction pipeline to produce an array of sub-features from a given IDataWindow or ILabeledDataWindow.
    FeatureGramNormalizer
    Provides normalization of each feature element of the feature vectors of the feature grams produced by an iterable.
    IdentityFeatureGramDescriptor
    A feature gram extractor that passes the contents of IDataWindow.getData() through as the feature gram on which models are trained and classifications are performed.
    LabeledFeatureGram<FDATA>
    Contains an array of features, generally computed from subwindows of a single IDataWindow, together with the labels from the source IDataWindow.

Package org.eng.aisp.feature Description

Defines a framework for features and the operations on them including extractiong and processing.
